net.sandius.rembulan

Interface MetatableAccessor

  • All Superinterfaces:
    MetatableProvider
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ExecutionContext, StateContext
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractStateContext

    public interface MetatableAccessor
extends MetatableProvider
    A metatable accessor, an interface for getting and setting object metatables.

    In Lua, only tables and (full) userdata carry their own metatables; for all other types of values T, all values of type T share a metatable. This interface provides a uniform setter for metatables of all types.

      • setMetatable

        Table setMetatable(Object instance,
                   Table table)
        Sets the metatable of the object instance to table. table may be null: in that case, clears instance's metatable. Returns the previous metatable.

        Note that instance may share the metatable with other instances of the same (Lua) type. This method provides a uniform interface for setting the metatables of all types.

        Parameters:
        instance - object to set the metatable of, may be null
        table - new metatable of instance, may be null
        Returns:
        the previous metatable of instance
